    "created_at": "2014-05-31T04:27:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-05-31T04:27:52Z",
    "body": "That's true, the use case of `prefer-dynamic` and `linkage=` are pretty limiting sadly as they only really affect executables, which is only one form of output the compiler can have. I wonder if we can tie the choice of linkage specifically to the choice of executable output?\n",
