    "created_at": "2015-02-22T23:56:37Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-02-22T23:56:37Z",
    "body": "It depends what you mean by standalone. Rust statically links against other Rust libraries by default, but not against the system libc (it's... not best practice to statically link against glibc, for example).\n\n(NB. this issue is about trying to improve the ability to diagnose when a Rust library can only be found in dynamic form, causing an application to be statically linked. It's just an improvement to an existing feature, not adding a new one.)\n",
